 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uriggen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Riggen</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 45<br> <font color=#333399>(3/7/02 6:00:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26228.topic&index=45>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: little tips</span><hr size=1> I just completed my set today and I must agree. Elysian is probably going to be my full-time BP for the remainder of my EQ career. I'll still go after a Kael RotG BP, but will just swap it in long enough for casting. It is shockingly easy to acquire Elysian compared to the time and effort required in the planes and in ToV. Remains seem to drop armor every five or six kills at most, and during the time I spent in Umbral I gave away 3 duplicate sets of legs, 4 boots, gloves, arms, and several bracers.<br>
<br>
I don't habitually solo. I'm alter-specced and while I consider myself a smart player, I probably don't know all the little timesaving tricks that a career soloer might have up their sleeves. All I did was pull and lock down, epic, arm dot, cast winged death, med and repeat casts as needed until the remains fell over. Nothing special. I spent mana on the side keeping PotG, Bladecoat, Eagle or Howler, and an occasional Regrowth up as buffs.<br>
<br>
Pulling singles was dead easy--I didn't even bother with Harmony. Elysians and their neighboring mobs don't appear to assist each other and aggro ranges are a good bit lower than in the planes.<br>
<br>
The remains spawn across a spectrum of levels I would estimate at between 54 and 57. The low end remains were so easy that I found myself ending fights sometimes with 80 mana. Yes, this is against the post-upgraded remains. Againt the most resist prone remains a fight rarely took more than ten minutes, and I ended with at least 40 mana. Even the absolute worst case where I was a little sloppy was no contest. On the two occasions where I had Koadic's, there was no downtime to speak of. One Elysian would die and seconds later I would be pulling another.<br>
<br>
I'm not going to say I'm not happy about Elysian's availability, but the risk/reward is strikingly out of line with what I've come to think of as &quot;normal&quot;. I can't help but believe that some kind of further nerfing is imminent.<br>
