<br>
I've spent here countless hours, solo and teaming up with <br>
druids of all levels.<br>
<br>
This is the armor of choice for me as well... wish i had<br>
regrowth of the grove... and it would be the only thing<br>
i really want out of the quest armor.. :)<br>
<br>
You can use harmony on all except the corrupted... which you<br>
shouldnt pull anyway, unless if with others who can slow/heal blahblah.<br>
<br>
Pulling more than one solo is just stupid, and a waste of time, IMHO, so if you do get more than one, gate or egress out.<br>
Egress works for me, as i use SOE + mask of hunter.<br>
If you use wolf form, do bare in mind that you'll end up without it, and a few feet from the zone line... just common sense. (if you use egress)<br>
<br>
Before going to the ruins just over the hill i run around the hill and check for freebie roamers... usually some up and around.<br>
You can be invis the whole time, just get close to the remains, and as they run at ya, just run back :)<br>
I usually make it back to the kite area with my invis still on.<br>
<br>
Dark Assassins, named, skeletal drudge, and elysians see invis.<br>
There is only 1 DA that wanders close to that house (ruins), and it is the only one you should really worry about.<br>
The aggro seems to be close to the line-of-sight, although clearly isnt, as i often see them and they dont attack :)<br>
<br>
Pathing is broken around some trees, do watch where your mob is running... <br>
<br>
I had wondered if light-sources emminating from some of the remains have anything to do with the armor they drop.<br>
So far, I've seen a bunch... most of the time it is just gems <br>
that elysians drop, except for one time when only boots droped and elysian had lightsource on it (and nothing else).<br>
<br>
Epic definately helps, although I would still do this solo without it.. the drop NERF BAT is imminent.  I know it.<br>
So get the armor while you can ;)<br>
I definately think either the drop rate will be 'tweaked', or<br>
elysians will start to summon... lets face it, they are 54-57.<br>
Maybe they'll put some mobs that path into the kite area...<br>
Either way.  Get yours now ;)<br>
<br>
This whole camp takes a lot shorter when you team with others.  Doing this with 5 or 6 druids in a group is very fun.<br>
I just pull 2 or 3 at a time .... <br>
<br>
Some gems that drop from them are worth good 70pp+.<br>
The skulls I assume are for some faction, or quest.<br>
Spells range from 52-54 in levels. (soe, mark of retribution, <br>
shaman dot...forget name)<br>
<br>
The drop rates werent all that great for me... <br>
It took a good number of these things to for the drops...<br>
but patience prevails... and all the pain is worth it in the end.<br>
<br>
Good luck.<br>
