I did this for the first time this weekend.  I killed a few solo then got a double pull and found that faster.  Took me 15 minutes to kill one using Epic/WD/Drones, and ending up at 1/2 mana.  Started doing two at a time and leaving out WD, did a pair in 25 minutes or so.  Each one needs to be rooted approximately 30 times with resists (not kidding).<br>
<br>
Doing two at a time was a rush, and I will come back to do it again (I love it when killing mobs is like the lottery).<br>
<br>
In 9 kills mixed over two short sessions, I got one drop - a tunic.  Another druid that was soloing there said the drop rate has been hit with the nerf stick, but I have little to compare it to.  I do know that the 2.5 hours or so that I was there was a lot less time to get a tunic than I spent in HoT so far without seeing one even drop. <p><BR><br><B><I><img src="http://www.druidmail.com/santerre2.gif">Santerre.</I></B></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukobara.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kobara</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 84<br> <font color=#333399>(3/21/02 1:32:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26228.topic&index=52>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: little tips</span><hr size=1> Drops are not nerfed yet... still see an average of 2 drops per 10 kills or so which has always seemed close to normal on these... dont try this without epic as a soloer, unless you have a pocket enchanter sitting there dealing you C2 or C3 and sponging some exp in exchange. Roots and even snares resist far more often than the time of the original posting here. Use the original poster's "guide" as a means to find the camp spot, but the rest is pretty much outdated info that could be updated to match current sit-rep of the zone in general. The Dark Assassin mentioned at zone entry no longer exists there, so Egress is now MUCH safer than the past and should be used without hesitation in case of a bad pull. Experience will go painfully slow solo, but if you are here for experience then you are in for disappointment. Hunt these for the armor drops or not at all in my opinion. Pathing still leaves the corner pull spot safe from roamers and the Disturbed Elysians remain the ONLY mobs in Umbral that do not summon. Verant obviously intended making these guys soloable by us or they would have changed the summon situation many patches ago. What they did was make it VERY difficult to do this without a LOT of mana (ie-high level) and without an epic to use) Get an Elysian that resists 5 or 6 roots during the kill, together with 2 to 3 resists on Winged Death or BoR, and mana can drop too fast. Leave yourself that 100 mana cushion you need for egress and use it if you are in trouble. Good luck on the drops if you choose to kill these solo. HPs I would estimate in the 18-20 K range, but hard to be sure since they spend much of the kill time moving, which results in decreased effectiveness of the DoTs used. Would be nice to see one that held root max time all thru the kill to get a closer idea, but the closest estimate came from parsing a melee battle when grouped once. That is where we found the 18-20 k figure. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukobara.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kobara</A> at: 3/21/02 9:53:58 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umilesgond.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Milesgond</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#333399>(3/21/02 5:00:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26228.topic&index=53>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: little tips</span><hr size=1> I actually managed to solo one of these without the epic..  was a huge pain in the @$$..  can't wait till my epic is finished!!   ;) <p>Milesgond Harelk <br>
